CamSys provides a camera object that will manage draws to the canvas
Author : Ryan Connors : rmconnor@ucsc.edu, ryanmconnors@gmail.com, ryan.connors@thefoundry.co.uk
Project: RisingTide


It provides the following functionality:
---------------------------------------
global variables :
      camera_speed : the step in pixels the camera will move when stepCam cam functions are called
---------------------------------------

Objects:
Camera 				:			This is an encapsulated object the contains details the camera uses to draw
								Properties:
									x 		   : Integer - x position of the camera
									y 		   : Integer - y position of the camera
									viewHeight : Integer - the height of the frame that will be drawn in pixels
									viewWidth  : Integer - the width of the frame that will be drawn in pixels
									

----------------------------------------
Functions:
Camera(x : Integer, y : Integer) 
: This constructs a new camera object, default draw dimension is undefined
: and must be set by mutation prior to drawing
							 
void moveCamera(cam : Camera, x : Integer, y : Integer)			 
: This relocates the camera to a new world location

void stepCameraX(cam : Camera)
: This steps the camera in the x direction by camera_speed pixels

void stepCameraY(cam : Camera)
: This steps the camera in the y direction by camera_speed pixels

void mutCamHeight(cam : Camera, height : Integer)
: Changes the current height of the camera draw to the height argument of pixels

void mutCamWidth(cam : Camera, width : Integer )
: Changes the current width of the camera draw to the width argument of pixels

void camUpdate(cam : Camera, objects : objects[]) 
: Updates the camera with a list of drawable tiles

void camDraw(cam : Camera, object : objects[] )
: Determines which objects should be drawn and draws them to canvas
							  
